post_text: At Falloween this year there will be a FREE golf carting service provided to/from the festival. The carts can be used for a variety of different reasons, all for FREE. Donations will still be accepted for anyone wanting to donate to the Walkerton NCSA Soccer program and John Glenn Boys Varsity Soccer. If you are in need of a ride, call Jeffrey Strycker at 574-279-1431 and we will help you out as soon as we can. This is the first year of providing this specific service, so please be patient. We will serve you as best as we can.

post_text:
Falloween Parade Grand Marshal this year will be Joshua Short. He's earned a Bachelor's degree in Broadcast Journalism from Columbia College Chicago. While there, he dabbled in radio, hosting two shows at an Arabic radio station (yes, he studied Arabic for 6 years). He's also earned multiple award nominations from the National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences.

As an intern in three different newsrooms, Joshua has covered some very big stories, including: Anti-Trump protests in Chicago, the NFL Draft in Grant Park and even traveled to Washington, D.C. to report on the 2017 Presidential Inauguration.

Joshua loves traveling, sightseeing and crime shows. He's also a big fan of reality TV, even scoring one-on-one interviews with TV personalities Jussie Smollett and Issa Rae while at Columbia.

With these unique experiences, he hopes to inform, confirm and educate through passionate storytelling and captivate viewers through his charismatic personality. Despite being only two hours from Chicago, Joshua considers South Bend his new home.
text:
Falloween Parade Grand Marshal this year will be Joshua Short. He's earned a Bachelor's degree in Broadcast Journalism from Columbia College Chicago. While there, he dabbled in radio, hosting two shows at an Arabic radio station (yes, he studied Arabic for 6 years). He's also earned multiple award nominations from the National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences.

As an intern in three different newsrooms, Joshua has covered some very big stories, including: Anti-Trump protests in Chicago, the NFL Draft in Grant Park and even traveled to Washington, D.C. to report on the 2017 Presidential Inauguration.

Joshua loves traveling, sightseeing and crime shows. He's also a big fan of reality TV, even scoring one-on-one interviews with TV personalities Jussie Smollett and Issa Rae while at Columbia.

With these unique experiences, he hopes to inform, confirm and educate through passionate storytelling and captivate viewers through his charismatic personality. Despite being only two hours from Chicago, Joshua considers South Bend his new home.

An Advance-Sale One day Wristband is available for $20 (each) through September 20th (noon) at all John Glenn Schools, at the TCU location in Walkerton, Plymouth or online. An advance-sale wristband may be used on any day for the entire day at the 2019 Falloween Fest. Sorry, no refunds.
An Advance-Sale Mega Wristband is available for $55 (each) through September 20th (noon) at John Glenn Schools and at the TCU location in Walkerton, Plymouth or online. You may also PURCHASE WRISTBANDS NOW online at any time by visiting www.falloweenfest.com (click on rides) OR at www.skerbeck.com (credit cards accepted at this site). An Advance-sale Mega Wristband may be used on all three days of the 2019 Falloween. Sorry, no refunds! The advance-sale mega wristbands are limited quantity being sold (they may run out prior to 9/20). This is a great deal! Plan to make your purchases early!

post_text: Come help support our JOHN GLENN HIGH SCHOOL GIRLS BASKETBALL TEAM, and participate in our "3 PT CHALLENGE" During FALLOWEEN FEST. $4 to shoot. Participants get 4 shots from 3 different spots. The last shot at each spot is the "MONEY BALL" worth 2 points for a possible of 15 points. If shooters make at least 4 points, they receive a prize from our 3rd place variety table. If they earn at least 6 points they will win a Basketball. If they hit at least 10 points they receive a Shirt, and a perfect score of 15 points they will win a 50" Flat Screen TV.
